---
const days = Array.from({ length: 30 }, (_, i) => i + 1);
---

<section class="finish-line section reveal">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="section-label">THE FINISH LINE</span>
    <h2>Day 30 is the last day. When you're done, you're done.</h2>
    <p class="text-body finish-line__body">
      This is not an ongoing subscription. Not an infinite content library. Not a program that quietly hopes you'll keep paying.
    </p>
    <p class="text-body finish-line__body">
      It's 30 sessions with a start and an end. Complete them in a month. Log every one. When you finish, you've met the standard.
    </p>
    <div class="finish-line__progress">
      {days.map((day) => (
        <div class={`finish-line__day ${day <= 28 ? 'finish-line__day--filled' : ''}`} />
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .finish-line__body {
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  .finish-line__body:last-of-type {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .finish-line__progress {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(30, 1fr);
    gap: 3px;
    max-width: 500px;
  }

  .finish-line__day {
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .finish-line__day--filled {
    background-color: var(--charcoal);
    border-color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .finish-line__progress {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(15, 1fr);
      gap: 3px;
      max-width: 300px;
    }
  }
</style>
